episodes.overview: Desperate and alone in a 3-year battle against an obsessive stalker, Di McDonald meets policewoman Beck Norris who takes on the case. Norris enlists the FBI profiler who caught the Unabomber, to bring Di's stalker to justice.

episodes.name: About a Boy
episodes.overview: Quaden is a nine-year-old with dwarfism who just wants to fit in. When his Mum posted a video of Quaden distraught after a tough day at school they couldn't have predicted what would unfold, as they triumphed over the trolls.

episodes.name: Finding Her Voice
episodes.overview: Singer Megan Washington went public with a 'shameful' secret six years ago and then stopped making music. In this update she describes the long road back to a new album and why the best art happens out of your comfort zone.

episodes.name: Fight for the Truth
episodes.overview: An outback town, a newspaper in trouble and an unlikely saviour. Broken Hill is fighting to keep its century-old newspaper alive but can the Barrier Truth's owners and loyal community steer it through its toughest time yet?

episodes.name: To His Door
episodes.overview: Serial killer Bradley Edwards hid in plain sight for nearly 25 years. Australian Story reveals the extraordinary twists and turns that led to police cracking the case and revisits the families of two of his victims.

episodes.name: A Matter of Minutes
episodes.overview: On Christmas Day two years ago Mick O'Dowd was feeling unwell. 24 hours later he was battling for his life. The life-affirming story of Mick and Katharine O'Dowd and the silent killer most people have never heard of.

episodes.name: Lest We Forget: The Australian Experience of Spanish Flu
episodes.overview: In the midst of the COVID lockdown, Australian Story undertook the ambitious task of delving through the archives and speaking to expert historians to produce the definitive piece on Spanish Flu. A special encore screening.

episodes.name: Cradle of Life / To Russia with Love
episodes.overview: In the season finale, Australian Story meets an 81-year-old inventor who's saved the lives of hundreds of premmie babies and checks in with the hilarious Dustyesky 'fake Russian' choir for a special Christmas performance.

episodes.name: Surviving Turbulence
episodes.overview: 16-year-old teen Bob Bramley takes to the skies to break a solo flying record and shine a light on youth mental health, galvanised by the desperate struggles of his two friends.

episodes.name: Sisters in Arms
episodes.overview: There's a hidden danger lurking in every home and these are the two mothers who've achieved a world first to protect our children.

episodes.name: The Tipping Point
episodes.overview: Scientist Veena Sahajwalla is a recycling revolutionary whose bold new ideas are helping reduce landfill. Now she's unveiling her latest brainchild, an invention which turns the discarded into the designer.

episodes.name: I Dream of Jeanne
episodes.overview: Unique and outrageous, Jeanne Little was the comedy dah-ling of daytime television in the 70s and 80s. Four months after her death from Alzheimers, daughter Katie reveals some intimate family secrets.

episodes.name: Fish Out of Water
episodes.overview: Promising young swimmer Shayna Jack was destined for the Olympics until she failed a routine drug test. But is the evidence against her justified or has she been caught up in an over-zealous anti-doping dragnet?

episodes.name: An Unlikely Match
episodes.overview: Drawing on her own experience of trauma, comedian Magda Szubanski forms an unlikely alliance with teenager Will Connelly, aka Eggboy, to help combat mental health issues in bushfire-ravaged communities.

episodes.name: Raising the Bar
episodes.overview: She's the glamorous lawyer representing high-profile clients like Julian Assange and Amber Heard. Jennifer Robinson charts her meteoric rise from small town public schoolgirl to the pinnacle of legal life in London.

episodes.name: Chamber of Silence
episodes.overview: Sexual slurs, baseless rumours, harassment and abuse - former Federal Labor minister Kate Ellis looks into Canberra's toxic culture, speaking to female politicians from all parties to call out systemic misogyny in parliament.

episodes.name: Sophie's Choice
episodes.overview: Mao's Last Dancer Li Cunxin and his wife and daughter's dramatic story of sacrifice, questioning and the painful journey towards reconciliation.

episodes.name: Birds of a Feather
episodes.overview: Identical twins Brigette and Paula Powers are so close they live and work together and even speak in unison. After a chance meeting with Steve Irwin, they now use their unique connection to save injured seabirds.

episodes.name: Forever Young
episodes.overview: A recent coronial inquest reveals the catastrophic errors made by NSW Police which left teenager Ursula Barwick's fate a mystery for almost 30 years.

episodes.name: Children of the Brush (Part 1)
episodes.overview: He's one of Australia's most successful and famous painters. But what has been the cost of fame for the children of acclaimed artist John Olsen?

episodes.name: Children of the Brush (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Part two of an inside look at one of Australia's greatest artistic dynasties. In this concluding episode, a court case threatens to derail the family of acclaimed painter John Olsen.

episodes.name: A World of their Own
episodes.overview: The Seekers blazed a trail for Australian music in the 1960s with a number of chart topping international hits. But fame led to fallout and they split at the height of their success. They reunite to reminisce about the ride.

episodes.name: A Balancing Act
episodes.overview: Dr Michelle Telfer is a world leader in providing treatment for children and teens with gender dysphoria, guiding them through their first steps towards transitioning. But her work isn't without its critics and controversies.

episodes.name: A Good Match
episodes.overview: When women's soccer star Rhali Dobson received an on-field marriage proposal, the pictures went viral around the world. It was a story of love, sport and sacrifice – and a heart-wrenching plot.

episodes.name: Final Call
episodes.overview: After his wife was murdered while working on call as a nurse in South Australia's remote APY Lands, Keith Woodford has campaigned for a coronial inquest which has delivered some breakthrough findings.

episodes.name: Bouncing Back
episodes.overview: An unlikely friendship forged on the tennis court between a homeless man and famous tennis pro leads to lifechanging events and a new beginning.

episodes.name: Luc Longley: One Giant Leap (Part 1)
episodes.overview: In the first of a two part special, we find out how a gentle kid from Fremantle ended up playing alongside Michael Jordan in the world's greatest team, the Chicago Bulls. Luc Longley's extraordinary story One Giant Leap.

episodes.name: Luc Longley: One Giant Leap (Part 2)
episodes.overview: From running with the Chicago Bulls to his omission from The Last Dance documentary, Luc Longley sets the record straight.

episodes.name: The Road to Justice
episodes.overview: A mother's battle to bring her daughter's killer to account pays off when a coroner's inquest leads to a breakthrough.

episodes.name: Saving MG99
episodes.overview: A daring sea rescue led by the Australian Navy saved 99 people from certain death. Forty years later, the survivors meet their saviours in an emotional reunion.

episodes.name: Home Straight
episodes.overview: In a case of life imitating art, iconic Aussie actor Michael Caton channels his beloved character from The Castle to fight for the underdog. Caton knows he's in the home straight of his life and wants to make the most of it.

episodes.name: Beyond the Grave
episodes.overview: One of the nation's biggest cold case mysteries takes a new turn when 'Somerton Man' is unearthed from an Adelaide cemetery in the hope that his DNA might finally reveal the secrets he took to his grave.

episodes.name: The Good Doctor
episodes.overview: Dr Jamal Rifi has given up his retirement dreams to fight COVID from his front yard in the middle of the nation's Delta outbreak.

episodes.name: No Place Like Home
episodes.overview: The story behind the story of the family at the centre of a tug of war between a small country town and the big end of government.

episodes.name: The Accomplice
episodes.overview: Behind the scenes of the AFP investigation into Australia's biggest insider trading case, where two young men united by deception are brought down by greed.

episodes.name: The Godfather of Coral
episodes.overview: Charlie Veron has spent his career underwater charting the world's coral wonderlands. Now, as the Great Barrier Reef faces its biggest threat, he reveals an audacious rescue plan.

episodes.name: California Dreaming
episodes.overview: Like the characters in his blockbuster novels, author Matthew Reilly is no stranger to persevering through loss and setback. Now he's realising the childhood dream that inspired his career - directing an action movie.

episodes.name: Unmasking Max
episodes.overview: Funnyman Max Gillies has been making people laugh all his life. Now at almost 80, he reveals the hidden family grief he has carried with him, and how comic acting became a welcome escape from his troubles at home as a child.

episodes.name: Happy Days
episodes.overview: The heartwarming next chapter of Australian Story's most popular program ever proves love really does conquer all. Checking in with Gayle and Mac Shann.

episodes.name: The Final Hurdle
episodes.overview: Athlete, mother of four and reality TV star Jana Pittman talks about her new life as a doctor and her regrets about the period when she was labelled 'Drama Jana'.

episodes.name: Justice for Justine
episodes.overview: A Sydney family takes on the Minneapolis police department in a long-running court battle to hold officer Mohamed Noor accountable for the death of Justine Ruszczyk.

episodes.name: In the Name of the Child
episodes.overview: Lauren Burns fought to find her anonymous sperm donor father. As she becomes a parent, she's back campaigning to make it easier for donor-conceived children to find their biological family, and make donations more accessible.

episodes.name: Grace Under Fire
episodes.overview: Outspoken Australian of the Year Grace Tame looks back over a tumultuous and life-changing 12 months.

episodes.name: Glenn McGrath: Bowled Over
episodes.overview: At home with Aussie cricket legend Glenn McGrath as he and his growing family continue to honour the legacy of his late wife Jane. His children James and Holly speak publicly for the first time about their mother's legacy.

episodes.name: Fakes
episodes.overview: After falling for a man whose life was a carefully constructed web of lies, journalist Stephanie Wood meets other women with uncannily similar experiences.

episodes.name: The Great Escapes
episodes.overview: Magician Arthur Coghlan's death-defying escapes in the 1970s earned him the title of Australia's Houdini. Now in his late 80s he reveals the stories behind his most terrifying stunts and how he's passed the magic onto his daughter.

episodes.name: Trials and Tribulations (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Having spent more than 12 years in jail for murder, Scott Austic was acquitted after revelations of planted evidence. Now the family of victim Stacey Thorne is demanding police reopen the investigation to find her killer.

episodes.name: Trials and Tribulations (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Having spent more than 12 years in jail for murder, Scott Austic was acquitted after sensational revelations. Now the family of victim Stacey Thorne is demanding police reopen the investigation to find her killer.

episodes.name: Into the Wild
episodes.overview: A young couple brave extreme weather and isolation to tackle Australia's extinction crisis, successfully reintroducing long-lost native animals back into the remote Sturt Desert.

episodes.name: Nicola Forrest: The Undercover Billionaire
episodes.overview: How the loss of her stillborn daughter set billionaire philanthropist Nicola Forrest and her husband Andrew on the path of pledging to give away the "vast majority" of their mining fortune.

episodes.name: Lisa Curry: The Deep End
episodes.overview: Former golden girl of the pool Lisa Curry has lived in the spotlight for decades. We've seen her weddings, babies and divorce. Now Lisa opens up about the heart-wrenching loss of her daughter Jaimi.

episodes.name: Bon Scott: On the Brink
episodes.overview: Bon Scott was set to become an international rock star with AC/DC when he died suddenly in 1980. Now for the first time, family and friends open up about his vulnerabilities and state of mind leading up to his untimely death.

episodes.name: Cathy McGowan: An Independent Woman
episodes.overview: Cathy McGowan is considered the "godmother" of the Independents movement that's dominating the election. The former member for Indi is also its secret weapon, sharing her insights with candidates across the country.

episodes.name: Kathy Lette: Letting Loose
episodes.overview: Co-author of Puberty Blues Kathy Lette has mined her life for stories since her teens. Now post-menopause, she opens up about her life and determination to age disgracefully.

episodes.name: Breaking Free
episodes.overview: A notorious bank robber destined for a life in prison discovers a new path when he confronts his hidden trauma. Now he's assisting others to seek justice for crimes long buried, but it's been a rocky road to redemption.

episodes.name: Shanna Whan: Last Drinks
episodes.overview: The story of how self-described 'small town drunk' Shanna Whan transformed her life to become Australian of the Year Local Hero and is now changing attitudes to booze in the bush.

episodes.name: The Songlines of Leah Purcell
episodes.overview: From dirt poor beginnings, actor, writer and director Leah Purcell is now at the top of her game, weaving her family's complicated history and her own troubled past into a powerful reimagining of a classic Australian tale.

episodes.name: A Community Undertaking
episodes.overview: In the working-class town of Port Kembla, a small funeral home is transforming the way we deal with death and sparking a quiet revolution in the process.

episodes.name: Jumping the Gun (Part 1)
episodes.overview: A devoted aunt investigates the mysterious death of her niece Amy Wensley, throwing doubt on the police case and exposing devastating investigative failures.

episodes.name: Jumping the Gun (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Concluding the story about the mysterious death of Amy Wensley. As her family fights for justice, they discover a flawed police investigation and devastating forensic oversights.

episodes.name: Lyn Dawson: Vanished
episodes.overview: Missing for 40 years, Lyn Dawson's sister and brother never gave up hope they'd find justice. Behind the scenes as her siblings prepare for the outcome of her husband Chris Dawson's murder trial and digest the guilty verdict.

episodes.name: David Pocock: A Whole New Ball Game
episodes.overview: Senate powerbroker of the moment David Pocock on the forces that drew him to politics and why his background as an international rugby star helped prepare him for his biggest test yet.

episodes.name: Fire Fight: Mick Tisbury
episodes.overview: One man's decade-long mission to expose the extent of an alarming chemical contamination scandal. Then, with no medical training, firefighter Mick Tisbury found an ingenious solution to help those who'd been exposed.

episodes.name: If You Build It - Greg Donovan
episodes.overview: When middle-aged insurance executive Greg Donovan was made redundant, he was told to play it safe. Instead he gambled his payout on a crazy idea to build the world's most remote music festival - and won.

episodes.name: In a Different League - Michael Cheika
episodes.overview: Controversial rugby coach Michael Cheika has never been in greater international demand. So why is he taking a lowly ranked team to the Rugby League World Cup?

episodes.name: Getting Heavy - Parkway Drive
episodes.overview: How five surfers from Byron Bay, in one of the biggest heavy metal bands in the world, turned to therapy to confront their past, save their career and rebuild their friendship.

episodes.name: A World of Their Own - The Seekers
episodes.overview: Remembering singing legend Judith Durham and the trailblazing band who put Australian music on the map.

episodes.name: Losing Faith
episodes.overview: When Citipointe Christian College issued an enrolment contract asking parents to agree homosexuality was a sin, the protests of students sparked a firestorm around the rights of religious schools to practise their beliefs.

episodes.name: A Star Is Torn - Tim Minchin
episodes.overview: After his dazzling career comes unstuck, musician, actor and provocateur Tim Minchin reassesses his comedy, questions the dangerous allure of fame, and finds home is where the heart is.

episodes.name: Life of Poh
episodes.overview: From a "nerd" named Sharon to one of Australia's most loved celebrity chefs - how Poh Ling Yeow has refined the art of reinvention and made peace with her past.

episodes.name: My Name is Charles - The Somerton Man
episodes.overview: After more than 70 years, one of Australia's most enduring mysteries - the identity of the "Somerton Man" - is finally solved.

episodes.name: Leaning In - Ita Buttrose
episodes.overview: As the ABC's 90th year draws to a close, Chair Ita Buttrose reflects on a life in the spotlight and how six decades as a pioneering female journalist and magazine editor helped prepare her for one of the ABC's toughest jobs.

episodes.name: The Transformer - Saul Griffith
episodes.overview: His ideas caught the eye of the US President. Now engineer Saul Griffith is making waves at home, joining his local community in an ambitious project to electrify their suburb and power it with renewables.

episodes.name: Game Changer
episodes.overview: Many parents worry their children are gaming to excess and don't know how to deal with it. Psychologist Wayne Warburton says he can help, with an Australia-first program tackling problem gaming. Will it work?

episodes.name: Diving in Deep (Part 1) - Valerie Taylor
episodes.overview: Valerie Taylor burst onto our TV screens in the '60s, stunning viewers by diving with dangerous sharks. She shares home movies, recalls acting in Skippy and reveals the moment that made her a shark advocate.

episodes.name: Diving in Deep (Part 2) - Valerie Taylor
episodes.overview: Shark legend Valerie Taylor takes us behind the scenes of the hit film Jaws and inside her campaign to save the grey nurse shark. Still diving at 87, she's inspiring a new generation of marine warriors.

episodes.name: Making a Scene - Claudia Karvan
episodes.overview: Actor and producer Claudia Karvan speaks openly about her chaotic childhood and the challenges of managing her late father's mental illness. And she reveals how she mines her unconventional life for her drama.

episodes.name: After The Fall - Mahboba Rawi and Sourosh Cina
episodes.overview: From a Sydney loungeroom, a mother and son take on a perilous mission to evacuate children and staff from their Afghan orphanages following the Taliban's return to power in 2021. Can they pull it off?

episodes.name: A Matter of Minutes - Mick and Katharine O'Dowd
episodes.overview: Mick O'Dowd has survived the unimaginable. He came close to death but lived. Three years after first telling his story, Mick is reclaiming his life and is back doing the things he loves.

episodes.name: Charting Her Course - Jessica Watson
episodes.overview: Love, loss and sailing the world solo: Jessica Watson takes us inside her amazing voyage as a teenage sailor, speaks about the grief of losing her partner, and a new feature film which has thrust her back into the spotlight.

episodes.name: Call of the River (Update) - Kate McBride
episodes.overview: Four years after alerting the world to mass fish kills in the Darling River, young farmer Kate McBride is taking her campaign to Canberra. She's determined to be a voice for the bush and fight for the river she loves.

episodes.name: Taking the Lead - Heather Mitchell
episodes.overview: Actor Heather Mitchell's life has been as dramatic off screen as it has on. And she's channelling those experiences into some of the greatest performances of her career.

episodes.name: After the Storm (Update) - Beth Heinrich
episodes.overview: One woman's decades-long quest for justice. Beth Heinrich was permanently changed by what she experienced as a teenager. Now in her 80s, she's spent almost half her lifetime chasing the Anglican Church to right past wrongs.

episodes.name: Labour of Love - Michelle and Jono Harley
episodes.overview: How a 52-year-old woman gave birth to her grandson. When Michelle couldn't have children, her mother offered to be a surrogate. Her sister-in-law did too. Now Michelle and her husband Jono have the family they dreamed of.

episodes.name: Changing Minds
episodes.overview: The remarkable story of a woman taking part in Australia's first psychedelic-assisted therapy trial. For Lindy Bok, it's a profound and deeply emotional experience as the treatment helps her confront anxiety around death.

episodes.name: A Brilliant Canvas - John Olsen
episodes.overview: A story of art, fame and family. The late John Olsen, one of our most beloved painters, had an obsessive focus on his work, often casting a shadow on those around him. John and family open up about art and the cost of fame.

episodes.name: Blind Leading The Blind - Mick Curran and Jamie Teh
episodes.overview: Mick and Jamie bonded over coding as teenagers. Now their brilliant tech idea is transforming lives around the world. Their software could have made them rich but instead they've kept it free to help the blind community.

episodes.name: Fight For Freedom - Kathleen Folbigg
episodes.overview: Australian Story's coverage of Kathleen Folbigg's case helped kickstart the scientific research that ultimately freed her. Watch the updated story of her fight for freedom over the last twenty years.

episodes.name: The Getting of Wisdom - Hugh van Cuylenburg
episodes.overview: Buried memories and family secrets - how hit podcaster Hugh van Cuylenburg's quest to help people gain a positive mindset took him on his own path of self-discovery and forced him to face some uncomfortable truths.

episodes.name: A Voice from the Heart - Megan Davis
episodes.overview: As a child, Megan Davis fell in love with the Constitution. Now she's a lawyer and a driving force behind the Voice referendum. She wants to change the nation's founding document in the hope of improving her peoples' lives.

episodes.name: Force of Nature - Gina Chick
episodes.overview: Her unconventional approach to surviving in the wild captured the public imagination. Now reality TV star Gina Chick shares how connecting with nature helped her through unimaginable loss.

episodes.name: A Family Legacy - Erica Packer
episodes.overview: Erica Packer, former wife of billionaire James Packer, opens up about the deadly genetic mystery shadowing her family and the scientists working to crack the code for thousands more Australians.

episodes.name: Atonement - Dean Yates
episodes.overview: War correspondent Dean Yates thought he was indestructible but when two of his staff were gunned down by the US military in Iraq, he & his family reached breaking point. Now he's trying heal the wounds of war and help others.

episodes.name: A Silver Lining (Part 1)
episodes.overview: When three Newcastle teens became overnight rock stars, their world exploded; huge concerts and crowds, intense fame and scrutiny. Ben and Chris from Silverchair take us on that rollercoaster ride and say it's a miracle they survived.

episodes.name: A Silver Lining (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Rockband Silverchair makes a comeback with its fifth album and a massive hit. But backstage, the wheels are falling off and the band finally fizzles out. For Ben and Chris, life after Silverchair proves to be bumpy too.

episodes.name: Sea Change - Sam Elsom
episodes.overview: Designer Sam Elsom shocked friends and family when he ditched fashion to farm seaweed. Now he has developed a product that radically reduces methane emissions from livestock. But can he convince farmers to get on board?

episodes.name: The Big Lap - Fiona MacDonald
episodes.overview: Once a popular kids' TV host, Fiona MacDonald is on the trip of a lifetime. Since being diagnosed with motor neurone disease two years ago, she's driving around Australia to raise money for research, and have fun on the way.

episodes.name: His Brilliant Careers (Update) - Sam Neill
episodes.overview: When beloved film and TV star Sam Neill received a shock diagnosis, it forced him to take stock of his life. Now the actor is living with a rare disease, but it hasn't stopped him doing the work he loves.

episodes.name: When Kylie Met Sami - Kylie Moore-Gilbert and Sami Shah
episodes.overview: When Kylie Met Sami: She was released from an Iranian prison only to find her husband had left her. He was reeling from the loss of his job and the end of his marriage. An awkward first date led to a second chance at love.

episodes.name: Never Too Late (Update) - Gregory Smith
episodes.overview: Five years after his first appearance on Australian Story, Dr Gregory Smith continues his astonishing transformation. Homeless and an addict for many years, Smith is now an academic, has received an OAM and found new love.

episodes.name: To Elle and Back - Libbi Gorr
episodes.overview: What ever happened to Elle McFeast? She wowed TV audiences in the 90s with her bold and brassy satire. Then a live interview derailed it all. McFeast's creator Libbi Gorr opens up about the fallout and fighting her way back.

episodes.name: Taking A Bow - Brett Yang and Eddy Chen
episodes.overview: Meet the violin virtuosos from Brisbane who ditched a classical career to create an online music comedy act. Now Brett Yang and Eddy Chen have gone viral and are playing sell-out concerts around the world.

episodes.name: Stepping Up - Elly-May Barnes
episodes.overview: Singer Elly-May Barnes on stepping out of her famous father Jimmy's musical shadow, on the long road to the spotlight and how she channels her physical challenges into a powerful cabaret act.

episodes.name: Big Talk - Annie Louey
episodes.overview: With little more than a briefcase full of old photos for clues, comedian Annie Louey unravels decades-old secrets in a bid to understand who her father really was.

episodes.name: An Open Mind - Professor Richard Scolyer
episodes.overview: A doctor puts his life on the line to try and cure his own brain cancer, using the very treatment he helped pioneer to save melanoma patients.

episodes.name: The Making of Mini - Katrina Gorry
episodes.overview: After the Matildas' World Cup glory, star midfielder Katrina Gorry introduces us to the tiny secret weapon who rekindled her love for the game.

episodes.name: Mama's on a Mission - Mechelle Turvey
episodes.overview: When the senseless death of teenager Cassius Turvey ignited fury across the nation, his mother Mechelle responded with a call for peace and unity.

episodes.name: Driven - Minjee and Min Woo Lee
episodes.overview: Sibling golf superstars Minjee and Min Woo Lee are like chalk and cheese, but they share the same goal - to be World No 1.

episodes.name: Call of Duty - Anjali Sharma
episodes.overview: School striker Anjali Sharma sued the government at 16. Now she's taking her fight for an end to fossil fuels to federal parliament, and the powerbrokers are listening.

episodes.name: Peter Garrett
episodes.overview: In an Australian Story special, former politician and Midnight Oil frontman Peter Garrett opens up to Leigh Sales about love, loss and living large.

episodes.name: On the Brink - Bon Scott
episodes.overview: Australian Story revisits the remarkable life of the late Bon Scott to celebrate the 50th anniversary of him joining AC/DC.

episodes.name: Patient Zero - Richard Scolyer
episodes.overview: Australian Story checks in on 2024 Australian of the Year Professor Richard Scolyer as he reaches a remarkable milestone in his revolutionary cancer treatment.

episodes.name: Out of the Wild - Gina Chick
episodes.overview: How life has changed for inaugural Alone Australia winner Gina Chick. In conversation with Leigh Sales.

episodes.name: Man Underground - Arnold Dix
episodes.overview: Locals know him as a flower farmer but Arnold Dix shot to global fame when he helped rescue 41 Indian workers from a tunnel collapse. It turns out Arnold is also a barrister, scientist, engineer and a very unlikely hero.

episodes.name: Out of the Chaos - Anna Coutts-Trotter
episodes.overview: When Federal Labor Minister Tanya Plibersek learned her daughter Anna had been abused during a high school relationship, it was the beginning of the family's brutal fight for justice. Now Anna Coutts-Trotter is on a mission to support other survivors grappling with the aftermath of abuse.

episodes.name: One in Seven Trillion - Leila McDougall
episodes.overview: Leila McDougall has been defying the odds since childhood. She's overcome dyslexia, beaten cancer, and after sneaking into acting school, has written, produced and starred in a feature film to help her farming community.

episodes.name: Face to Fake - Chelsea Bonner
episodes.overview: Modelling agent Chelsea Bonner has spent her career fighting to change perceptions of beauty but now she has an even bigger battle on her hands - artificial intelligence.

episodes.name: Off Menu - Josh Niland
episodes.overview: Josh Niland's arguably Australia's hottest chef right now with his revolutionary approach to fish. The genesis of his wild experimentation: a life and death battle in childhood and the fear of failure as a young restaurateur.

episodes.name: Off Menu - Shaun Christie-David
episodes.overview: He can't cook, he's not after money but Shaun Christie-David is building a restaurant empire that's changing lives one dish at a time.

episodes.name: Off Menu - Kylie Kwong
episodes.overview: Kylie Kwong has been at the top of the Australian food scene for three decades. Now she reveals her surprising next chapter, as she continues to channel unimaginable grief into a force for good.

episodes.name: On The Outside Looking In - Cold Chisel
episodes.overview: As rock band Cold Chisel marks its 50th anniversary, we explore why the iconic group has made such a lasting impact on Australian culture.

episodes.name: The War Pup - Quaden Bayles
episodes.overview: When Quaden Bayles was nine, he was bullied and trolled for having dwarfism. But he also caught the eye of Mad Max director George Miller, and now at 13, has emerged triumphant.

episodes.name: Nick Cave with Leigh Sales
episodes.overview: Rock legend Nick Cave sits down with Leigh Sales for a wide-ranging and deeply personal conversation.

episodes.name: Flashpoint - Senator Fatima Payman
episodes.overview: A matter of conscience or act of betrayal? Former Labor Senator Fatima Payman reveals the inner torment behind breaking ranks to vote against her party and the fallout that followed, at home and in the capital.

episodes.name: Dead Funny - Michelle Brasier
episodes.overview: Comedian Michelle Brasier was told she had a 97 per cent chance of getting cancer. She chose to laugh about it.

episodes.name: This is How It Goes - Missy Higgins
episodes.overview: Singer-songwriter Missy Higgins says she's never felt more vulnerable in her life. One of our most accomplished female artists, Missy retraces her rise to the top and reveals the emotional turmoil of the past couple of years.

episodes.name: Making Lachlan Murdoch - Part 1: Blood
episodes.overview: The first of three episodes examines the forces that shaped the media heir and the roots of the Murdoch sibling rivalry.

episodes.name: Making Lachlan Murdoch - Part 2: Money
episodes.overview: In Part 2, Lachlan Murdoch feels the push and pull of the family business as he proves himself to his father.

episodes.name: Making Lachlan Murdoch - Part 3: Power
episodes.overview: In the final chapter, Lachlan Murdoch finally wins the long struggle to take over the family empire. But at what cost?

episodes.name: Leading Man - Michael Theo
episodes.overview: How Love on the Spectrum and Austin's Michael Theo found his voice and became a global star.

episodes.name: Holding On - Gus Taylor
episodes.overview: Two rock climbing accidents dealt Gus Taylor devastating blows. But now he realises climbing is the best teacher he's ever had.

episodes.name: Betrayal - Hannah Grundy
episodes.overview: A mysterious email. Shocking revelations. And the ultimate betrayal. How teacher Hannah Grundy was forced to become her own detective to unmask a sick cyber criminal whose identity she couldn't believe.

episodes.name: The Two of Us - Yael Stone and Jack Manning Bancroft
episodes.overview: When Orange Is the New Black star Yael Stone turned her back on Hollywood, everyone thought she was crazy - except the man who loved her. Social entrepreneur Jack Manning Bancroft knows what it takes to put skin in the game.

episodes.name: The Big Lap - Remembering Fiona MacDonald
episodes.overview: In memory of TV host Fiona MacDonald, who died this month from MND, we revisit her story, filmed as she drove around Australia with her sister to raise awareness of the disease.

episodes.name: Holding Ground - Chris Henggeler
episodes.overview: In one of the toughest parts of Australia, renegade pastoralist Chris Henggeler is trialling a bold idea to regenerate his land using feral pests. Now, he's found himself on the wrong side of the law.

29.name: Series 2024
29.overview: The power of the personal. Compelling stories about real people that illuminate, entertain and inspire. Presented by Leigh Sales.
